In[3]:
# 1. Cargar los datos
df = pd.read_csv('../../train.csv')

# 2. Crear la variable de respuesta categrica basada en los terciles del precio de venta
tercil_1 = df['SalePrice'].quantile(1/3)
tercil_2 = df['SalePrice'].quantile(2/3)

# Crear la categora de precio
df['PriceCategory'] = pd.cut(
    df['SalePrice'], 
    bins=[0, tercil_1, tercil_2, float('inf')], 
    labels=['Econmica', 'Intermedia', 'Cara']
)

# 3. Seleccionar las caractersticas para el modelo
selected_features = [
    'OverallQual',    # Calidad general
    'GrLivArea',      # rea habitable
    'GarageCars',     # Capacidad del garaje
    'YearBuilt',      # Ao de construccin
    'TotalBsmtSF',    # Superficie total del stano
    'FullBath',       # Baos completos
    'Neighborhood',   # Vecindario (categrica)
    'ExterQual',      # Calidad del exterior (categrica)
    'KitchenQual',    # Calidad de la cocina (categrica)
    'BsmtQual'        # Calidad del stano (categrica)
]

# 4. Preparar los datos
X = df[selected_features].copy()
y = df['PriceCategory']

Transformaciones

In[7]:
# Manejar valores faltantes en caractersticas numricas
numeric_features = X.select_dtypes(include=['int64', 'float64']).columns
imputer = SimpleImputer(strategy='median')
X[numeric_features] = imputer.fit_transform(X[numeric_features])

# Manejar valores faltantes en caractersticas categricas
categorical_features = X.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns
X[categorical_features] = X[categorical_features].fillna('None')

# Dividir los datos en conjunto de entrenamiento y prueba
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y
)
In[8]:
numeric_preprocessor = Pipeline(
    steps=[("imputer", SimpleImputer(strategy="median")), ("scaler", StandardScaler())]
)

# Se preparan los preprocesadores
categorical_preprocessor = OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown="ignore")

# Se transforman las colunas usando los preprocesadores
from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer

preprocesador = ColumnTransformer([
    ('one_hot_encoder',categorical_preprocessor,categorical_features),
    ('numerico', numeric_preprocessor,numeric_features)
],remainder="passthrough")

7. Anlisis de sobreajuste/desajuste

In[15]:
# Evaluar sobreajuste en los modelos SVM
models = {
    'SVM Lineal': modelGS_svc_lineal,
    'SVM Polinomial': modelGS_svc_poly,
    'SVM RBF': modelGS_svc_rbf
}

# Comparar rendimiento en train vs test
for name, model in models.items():
    train_accuracy = model.score(X_train, y_train)
    test_accuracy = model.score(X_test, y_test)
    diff = train_accuracy - test_accuracy
    
    print(f"{name}:")
    print(f"  Precisin train: {train_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"  Precisin test: {test_accuracy:.4f}")
    print(f"  Diferencia: {diff:.4f}")
    
    if diff > 0.1:
        print("  DIAGNSTICO: Posible sobreajuste")
    elif test_accuracy < 0.7:
        print("  DIAGNSTICO: Posible subajuste")
    else:
        print("  DIAGNSTICO: Ajuste adecuado")

# Visualizar curva de aprendizaje para el mejor modelo
from sklearn.model_selection import learning_curve

def plot_learning_curve(model, X, y, cv=5):
    train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(
        model, X, y, cv=cv, n_jobs=-1, 
        train_sizes=np.linspace(.1, 1.0, 10))
    
    train_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
    train_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
    test_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
    test_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.title("Curva de Aprendizaje")
    plt.xlabel("Tamao del conjunto de entrenamiento")
    plt.ylabel("Puntuacin")
    plt.grid()
    
    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_mean - train_std,
                     train_mean + train_std, alpha=0.1, color="r")
    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_mean - test_std,
                     test_mean + test_std, alpha=0.1, color="g")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, train_mean, 'o-', color="r", label="Entrenamiento")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, test_mean, 'o-', color="g", label="Validacin cruzada")
    plt.legend(loc="best")
    plt.show()

# Encontrar el mejor modelo
best_model_name = max(models.items(), key=lambda x: x[1].score(X_test, y_test))[0]
best_model = models[best_model_name]
print(f"Analizando curva de aprendizaje para {best_model_name}")
plot_learning_curve(best_model, X, y)

# Mtricas detalladas para cada modelo
import time


for name, model in models.items():
    start_time = time.time()
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    end_time = time.time()
    process_time = end_time - start_time
    
    print(f"\n--- {name} ---")
    print(f"Tiempo de procesamiento: {process_time:.5f} segundos")
    print(f"Precisin: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}")
    
    # Matriz de confusin
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues')
    plt.title(f"Matriz de Confusin - {name}")
    plt.xlabel("Prediccin")
    plt.ylabel("Real")
    plt.show()
    
    # Reporte detallado
    print("\nReporte de clasificacin:")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
    
    # Anlisis de errores
    errors = np.where(y_pred != y_test)[0]
    print(f"Total de errores: {len(errors)}")
    if len(errors) > 0:
        print("Distribucin de errores:")
        error_df = pd.DataFrame({
            'Real': y_test.iloc[errors],
            'Prediccin': y_pred[errors]
        })
        print(error_df['Real'].value_counts())
        print("\nTipos de errores:")
        print(error_df.groupby(['Real', 'Prediccin']).size())

# Comparacin visual de mtricas
metrics_data = []
for name, model in models.items():
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    report = classification_report(y_test, y_pred, output_dict=True)
    
    for category in ['Econmica', 'Intermedia', 'Cara']:
        metrics_data.append({
            'Modelo': name,
            'Categora': category,
            'Precisin': report[category]['precision'],
            'Recall': report[category]['recall'],
            'F1-Score': report[category]['f1-score']
        })

metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics_data)

# Grficos de comparacin
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))

plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
sns.barplot(x='Modelo', y='Precisin', hue='Categora', data=metrics_df)

# Comparar SVM con otros algoritmos
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
import time
from sklearn.preprocessing import FunctionTransformer

# Funcin para convertir matrices dispersas a densas
def to_dense(X):
    return X.toarray() if hasattr(X, 'toarray') else X

# Modificar los modelos para convertir datos dispersos
models_to_compare = {
    'SVM (Mejor)': best_model,
    'rbol de Decisin': make_pipeline(preprocesador, DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)),
    'Random Forest': make_pipeline(preprocesador, RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42)),
    'Naive Bayes': make_pipeline(preprocesador, FunctionTransformer(to_dense), GaussianNB()),
    'KNN': make_pipeline(preprocesador, KNeighborsClassifier()),
    'Regresin Logstica': make_pipeline(preprocesador, LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42))
}

# Entrenar y evaluar cada modelo
results = []

for name, model in models_to_compare.items():
    if name != 'SVM (Mejor)':
        print(f"Entrenando {name}...")
        start_train = time.time()
        model.fit(X_train, y_train)
        train_time = time.time() - start_train
    else:
        train_time = None
    
    # Medir tiempo de prediccin
    start_pred = time.time()
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    pred_time = time.time() - start_pred
    
    # Calcular mtricas
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    
    results.append({
        'Modelo': name,
        'Precisin': accuracy,
        'Tiempo de entrenamiento': train_time,
        'Tiempo de prediccin': pred_time
    })

# Crear dataframe con resultados
results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
print(results_df)

# Visualizar comparativa
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))

plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)
sns.barplot(x='Modelo', y='Precisin', data=results_df)
plt.title('Comparacin de Precisin entre Algoritmos')
plt.ylim(0.6, 1.0)
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)
sns.barplot(x='Modelo', y='Tiempo de prediccin', data=results_df)
plt.title('Comparacin de Tiempo de Prediccin')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Crear modelo de regresin con SVM
from sklearn.svm import SVR
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score, mean_absolute_error
import math

# Preparar variable para regresin
y_reg = df['SalePrice']

# Divisin de datos para regresin
X_train_reg, X_test_reg, y_train_reg, y_test_reg = train_test_split(
    X, y_reg, test_size=0.3, random_state=42
)

# Crear modelos con diferentes kernels
svr_models = {
    'SVR Lineal': make_pipeline(preprocesador, SVR(kernel='linear')),
    'SVR Polinomial': make_pipeline(preprocesador, SVR(kernel='poly', degree=3)),
    'SVR RBF': make_pipeline(preprocesador, SVR(kernel='rbf'))
}

# Evaluar modelos base
for name, model in svr_models.items():
    print(f"Entrenando {name}...")
    model.fit(X_train_reg, y_train_reg)
    
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_reg)
    
    # Mtricas
    rmse = math.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test_reg, y_pred))
    r2 = r2_score(y_test_reg, y_pred)
    
    print(f"RMSE: {rmse:.2f}")
    print(f"R: {r2:.4f}")
    
    # Visualizar predicciones
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.scatter(y_test_reg, y_pred, alpha=0.5)
    plt.plot([y_test_reg.min(), y_test_reg.max()], 
             [y_test_reg.min(), y_test_reg.max()], 
             'r--')
    plt.xlabel('Precio real')
    plt.ylabel('Precio predicho')
    plt.title(f'Predicciones vs Reales - {name}')
    plt.show()

# Ajuste de hiperparmetros para el mejor modelo (ejemplo con RBF)
print("Optimizando modelo SVR con kernel RBF...")
param_grid_svr = {
    'svr__C': [0.1, 1, 10, 100],
    'svr__gamma': ['scale', 'auto', 0.01, 0.1, 1],
    'svr__epsilon': [0.01, 0.1, 0.2]
}

grid_svr = GridSearchCV(
    svr_models['SVR RBF'], 
    param_grid_svr, 
    cv=5, 
    scoring='neg_mean_squared_error',
    n_jobs=-1
)

grid_svr.fit(X_train_reg, y_train_reg)
print("Mejores parmetros:", grid_svr.best_params_)

# Evaluar modelo optimizado
y_pred_best = grid_svr.predict(X_test_reg)
rmse_best = math.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test_reg, y_pred_best))
r2_best = r2_score(y_test_reg, y_pred_best)

print(f"RMSE con modelo optimizado: {rmse_best:.2f}")
print(f"R con modelo optimizado: {r2_best:.4f}")

# Visualizar resultados del modelo optimizado
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(y_test_reg, y_pred_best, alpha=0.5)
plt.plot([y_test_reg.min(), y_test_reg.max()], 
         [y_test_reg.min(), y_test_reg.max()], 
         'r--')
plt.xlabel('Precio real')
plt.ylabel('Precio predicho')
plt.title('Predicciones vs Reales - SVR Optimizado')
plt.show()

# Comparar con modelos de regresin anteriores
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

reg_models = {
    'SVR (Optimizado)': grid_svr,
    'Regresin Lineal': make_pipeline(preprocesador, LinearRegression()),
    'rbol de Regresin': make_pipeline(preprocesador, DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=42)),
    'Random Forest': make_pipeline(preprocesador, RandomForestRegressor(random_state=42)),
    'KNN Regressor': make_pipeline(preprocesador, KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5))
}

# Entrenar y evaluar
reg_results = []

for name, model in reg_models.items():
    if name != 'SVR (Optimizado)':
        print(f"Entrenando {name}...")
        model.fit(X_train_reg, y_train_reg)
    
    start_time = time.time()
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_reg)
    pred_time = time.time() - start_time
    
    # Mtricas
    rmse = math.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test_reg, y_pred))
    r2 = r2_score(y_test_reg, y_pred)
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test_reg, y_pred)
    
    reg_results.append({
        'Modelo': name,
        'RMSE': rmse,
        'R': r2,
        'MAE': mae,
        'Tiempo prediccin': pred_time
    })

# Crear dataframe y visualizar
reg_df = pd.DataFrame(reg_results)
print(reg_df)

# Visualizacin comparativa
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
sns.barplot(x='Modelo', y='RMSE', data=reg_df)
plt.title('Comparacin de RMSE')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
sns.barplot(x='Modelo', y='R', data=reg_df)
plt.title('Comparacin de R')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
sns.barplot(x='Modelo', y='MAE', data=reg_df)
plt.title('Comparacin de MAE')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
sns.barplot(x='Modelo', y='Tiempo prediccin', data=reg_df)
plt.title('Comparacin de Tiempo de Prediccin')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
